{panel:title=Atlassian Update - 16 February 2021|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#2684ff|titleBGColor=#2684ff|bgColor=#ffffff}
We are excited to announce that we have moved tabs back to the left hand side of Jira Cloud's new issue view. By moving tabs to the left admins are able to make better use of the space available on the issue view and create layouts that work for every member of their team. You can find our more in our [official announcement|https://community.atlassian.com/t5/New-to-Jira-discussions/Tabs-are-now-on-the-left-hand-side-of-Jira-Cloud-s-issue-view/m-p/1614901].
{panel}
We need more control and ease of finding fields.  If you take the Tabs and turn them into collapsible groupings on the sidebar it will make the sidebar usable when you have a large number of fields. Right now it's near impossible to find a field.

Collapsible groupings based on the tabs respecting field and tab order will fix a large part of our frustration with the new issue view.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Jira Cloud*. Using *Jira Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-65521].
  {panel}

As an Administrator, I would like to be able to disable public access to JIRA, so the users will have to log in before they can browse projects, search issues or navigate to system dashboard

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
 *NOTE:* This is a duplicate of [JRACLOUD-68967 | https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-68967]. Please follow [JRACLOUD-68967 | https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-68967]for updates. 
{panel}



 Allow users to be able to specify the position of a custom field in Jira issue view screen. Currently, this is positioned by default and the user has no control over it.

h3. Summary

Apps with webItems defined as:

{code}
{
	"url": "/view/clone-dialog.do?issueId={issue.id}&projectId={project.id}&projectKey={project.key}",
	"location": "transitions-all",
	"context": "page",
	"weight": 5,
	"tooltip": {
		"value": "Clone Test Run",
		"i18n": "clone_test_run"
		},
	"target": {
		"type": "dialog",
		"options": {
			"chrome": false,
			"size": "x-large"
			}
	},
	"key": "qmetry-mobile-test-run-clone",
	"name": {
		"value": "Clone Test Run",
		"i18n": "clone_test_run"
		}
}
{code}

does not display in the new issue view transitions unlike the old view (see screenshot for comparison)

h3. Workaround
Use {{"jira.issue.tools"}} location
